      },
      "date": "2019-10-31 22:35:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nPatch seems correct, but as stated in LU-12856 it isn't clear if this is going to fix the problem.  The flags field is zeroed at allocation time, so it is unlikely that the OBD_FL_SHORT_IO bit would be set randomly without OBD_MD_FLFLAGS being set, but I'm open to being wrong about that (e.g. if the buffer is re-used or something).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d1d01a192f21b5bc1d9b68cd508c6b7aee769e9c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 799,
